      "review_summary": "The PR adds operation/skip parameters to the Nix-mode config write guard and relaxes `doctorCommand` so Nix mode only blocks gateway-token generation up front.\n\nPR surface: Source +31. Total +31 across 2 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. source-reproducible: current main checks Nix mode before doctor repair sequencing, and auth paste/login paths can still reach guarded config updates after auth-store writes. I did not run a live Nix/OAuth CLI flow in this read-only review.",
